<p class="govuk-body">
    This website is run by DVSA on behalf of the Traffic Commissioners for Great Britain, the Department for
    Infrastructure Northern Ireland and the International Road Haulage Permits.
</p>
<p class="govuk-body">
    We want as many people as possible to be able to use this website. For example, that means you should be able to:
</p>

<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
    <li>zoom in up to 300% without the text spilling off the screen</li>
    <li>navigate most of the website using just a keyboard</li>
    <li>navigate most of the website using speech recognition software</li>
    <li>listen to most of the website using a screen reader (including the most recent versions of JAWS, NVDA and
        VoiceOver)
    </li>
</ul>

<p class="govuk-body">
    The text on the website should also be as simple as possible to understand.
</p>

<p class="govuk-body">
    <a class="govuk-link" title="External link to ability net webpage" target="_blank"
       href="https://mcmw.abilitynet.org.uk/">AbilityNet</a> has advice on making your device easier to use if you have
    a disability.
</p>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-l">How accessible this website is</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">
    We know some parts of this website aren’t fully accessible:
</p>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
    <li>some of our controls, content and status messages are hidden or not announced to screen readers and voice input
        software.
    </li>
    <li>some of our pages are difficult to navigate using just the keyboard or gestural input.</li>
    <li>some of our tables are complex and difficult to navigate using a screen reader.</li>
    <li>some of our links, buttons and messages are of sizes and/or colours that are difficult to read.</li>
    <li>some of our error messages do not provide enough information to enable a user to correct the error.</li>
    <li>some of our page titles and link titles do not adequately describe the purpose of the page or link.</li>
    <li>the structure of some of our pages means that information is not conveyed in a logical order.</li>
    <li>we use some custom controls which will be unfamiliar in the way they appear and operate .</li>
    <li>our service has a timeout which might interfere with users completing tasks.</li>
</ol>

